SIMPLE: truly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truly
<hw>Tru"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>True</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a true manner; according to
truth; in agreement with fact; <as>as, to state things <ex>truly</ex>;
the facts are <ex>truly</ex> represented</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I can not <qex>truly</qex> say how I came here.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exactly; justly; precisely; accurately; <as>as, to
estimate <ex>truly</ex> the weight of evidence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Sincerely; honestly; really; faithfully; <as>as, to
be <ex>truly</ex> attached to a lover</as>; the citizens are
<xex>truly</xex> loyal to their prince or their country.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Conformably to law; legally; legitimately.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His innocent babe [is] <qex>truly</qex> begotten.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>In fact; in deed; in reality; in truth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Beauty is excelled by manly grace⟦br⟧
And wisdom, which alone is <qex>truly</qex> fair.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trump</ent>⟦br⟧
